      <hedline>
        <hl1>Research on Many Fronts</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Daniel J Levitin letter on Dec 31 article about his research into music and the brain</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your article on my research into music and the brain [''Music of the Hemispheres'' by Clive Thompson, Dec. 31] prompted a letter writer to express her distress at the limitations of my work. I agree such research should include mothers' singing to their infants. But this requires specialized methods, and there are excellent scientists -- Sandra Trehub, Anne Fernald, Laurel Trainor -- pursuing just this question. They have discovered fascinating things about the human experience through parent-child musical interactions. (Yes, it can be measured.)</p>
        <p>Daniel J. Levitin  Montreal</p>
      </block>
